# PortDiary core

## Stack
- Frontend: React + Vite (`src/`)
- Backend: Node + Express + Postgres (`backend/`)
- Prices: Yahoo Finance; Thai tickers use `-BK` / SET market

## Key paths
| Area | Paths |
|------|--------|
| Report | `src/components/PortfolioReport.jsx`, `src/lib/reportScope.js`, `src/components/report/` |
| Overview chart | `src/components/charts/PortfolioChart.jsx` |
| History / TWR | `backend/src/lib/portfolioHistory.js` |
| Holdings sync | `backend/src/lib/holdingSync.js` |
| FX | `src/lib/currency.js`, `backend/src/lib/currency.js` |
| Tickers | `src/lib/ticker.js`, `backend/src/lib/ticker.js` |
| Transactions | `src/components/modals/TransactionModal.jsx`, `backend/src/routes/transactions.js` |

## Defaults when changing money or charts
- KPIs use live holdings (`price × shares`); history charts use transaction-derived series + TWR
- Never sum THB + USD amounts without `convertAmount`
- `portfolios.currency` in DB may be stale — use `inferPortfolioCurrency` from holdings
- After fixing `holdingSync`, run or add migration `rebuildHoldingsFromTransactions` for existing users
- Prefer project skills in `.cursor/skills/` for chart, holding, and deploy workflows
